}

^["validation"]{
 hypotheses: [#shared_register_projection_reduces_duplication, #complete_operator_semantics_reduce_decorative_grammar, #portable_inspect_is_teachable, #block_host_can_precede_parser_runtime, #prefix_postfix_paths_can_normalize, #semantic_reflection_preserves_truth, #charge_bias_can_be_inspectable, #safe_noop_preserves_exploration, #fractal_repetition_improves_learnability]
 negative_controls: [#route_structure_unchanged, #visual_voice_preserved]
 demo_path: ["/", "/topics/software/", "/topics/software/pretext/", "#local_pivot"]
}

^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - The current site already has semantic tagging, frame activation, and lightweight eventing, but it still treats hover and page-local modules as stronger organizing surfaces than mobile-first regions and shared runtime state.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - `site.js` owns global frame/mode activation and the spirit easter egg, while `frame-navigator.js` separately owns `g`, `[ ]`, `/`, and `Escape`; this is enough machinery to prove the next gap is arbitration and shared runtime, not lack of metaphoric vocabulary.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - `spw-component-semantics.js` already derives kind, form, role, liminality, and selection, which makes it the natural bridge from authored semantics into portable runtime intent.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - CSS is already rich in hover states and floating surfaces, but the governing model is not yet explicitly mobile-first; region ownership and coarse-pointer behavior remain implicit.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] decide - Plan around four foundations: named page regions, portable inspect/invoke semantics, shared inspectable registers, and block/script host contracts.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] taste - Keep magic summonable and inspectable; the calm default should survive even as the runtime surface deepens.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:12] decide - Wrote a distilled semantics note so future implementation can test counterexamples instead of letting metaphor drift across modules.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:12] verify - `poll-review.sh --scope=changed` passed cleanly for the new plan surfaces and `.spw` artifacts.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] decide - The user is not attached to current keybindings, which means the runtime can center semantic symmetry rather than preserving arbitrary legacy keys.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] revise - The plan now treats prefix/postfix symmetry, brace pivots, and structural wonder as first-class UX constraints instead of secondary aesthetic concerns.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] taste - Wonder should arrive as a pivot into clearer structure while preserving orientation, not as decorative motion layered onto already-legible surfaces.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] rebase - Refreshed `base_ref` to the current `main` commit after the plan artifact landed so the maintenance surface matches the active lineage.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:08] decide - Spw symmetry should be treated as more than prefix/postfix parity: visual surfaces, keyboard paths, touch paths, and semantic HTML reflection should converge on the same runtime facts.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:08] observe - The site already uses meaningful landmarks, heading structure, and aria state in many places; the missing step is to elevate that accessibility tree into the canonical reflection surface instead of treating it as a parallel concern.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:08] decide - Fractal geometry is useful here only as recursive surface structure: page -> region -> frame -> panel -> widget -> node should repeat the same boundary, name, inspect, pivot, and return logic across scales.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:08] taste - Intuitive reflection on the modern web should feel like native semantic HTML becoming deeper and more self-similar under inspection, not like an abstract math story pasted onto arbitrary markup.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:08] rebase - Refreshed `base_ref` to the current `main` commit while integrating symmetry, accessibility, and fractal-surface considerations.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:36] decide - Every operator should have inspectable interaction semantics before it is allowed to function as behavior; color alone is not enough.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:36] revise - The metaphysics model now treats charge and projection bias as bounded, inspectable runtime tendencies rather than hidden magical state.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:36] decide - No-response interaction paths are valid only when they preserve exploration: invoke, inspect, explain unavailable state, or pass through without trapping focus/register state.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:36] verify - Expanded the executable operator registry so visible sigils can carry operator type, intent, and interaction metadata across the full operator family.
 >>[2026-04-09 22:36] rebase - Refreshed `base_ref` to current `main` after the SVG/Pretext/reflection plan commit.
 >>[2026-04-09] style - Interaction semantics is personal style. The timing quality of a brace pivot, the texture of an inspect reveal, the decay rate of charge — these are aesthetic decisions, not just engineering constants. They should be made deliberately and logged as taste choices in the stream, not derived from whatever browser defaults happen to provide.
 >>[2026-04-09] observe - The spirit cycle already exists as a site-level metaphor with five phases (initiation, resistance, transformation, expression, return). If any interaction sequence can trace a phase, that tracing should be legible enough to inspect and reversible enough to not trap the visitor in a phase they cannot identify.
 >>[2026-04-09] style - Interaction style on this site will become recognizable through three qualities: timing texture (not speed, but quality of pace — does it feel deliberate or snappy?), reversibility depth (how far back can the visitor return without losing address?), and inspect legibility (does revealing a node feel more like reading or like touching?). Each of those is a taste decision to be made and logged.
}

^["open"]{
 ?[regions]: "Which page regions should be universal across routes versus optional per-surface?"
 ?[intent]: "What is the smallest portable interaction vocabulary that cleanly spans touch, pointer, and keyboard?"
 ?[registers]: "Which runtime registers must be first-class before navigator and console can become honest projections?"
 ?[blocks]: "What host contract should exist before Spw blocks and scripts are allowed to shape UI?"
 ?[symmetry]: "What is the canonical normalization from prefix and postfix interaction paths into one semantic register trace?"
 ?[operators]: "What exact runtime behavior, inspect state, or unavailable explanation should each operator expose on first implementation?"
 ?[reflection]: "What is the canonical normalization from visual runtime state into the HTML accessibility tree and other semantic reflection surfaces?"
 ?[a11y]: "Which native HTML structures should be considered the primary semantic hosts for regions, pivots, lenses, and block-backed components?"
 ?[fractal]: "Which recursive scale model is operational enough to improve learnability without turning fractal language into metaphor drift?"
 ?[charge]: "Which braces are allowed to store charge, what creates it, how does it decay, and which projections may it bias?"
 ?[no_response]: "What is the visible or semantic feedback threshold for no-op and unavailable interactions?"
 ?[pivots]: "Which structure changes count as local pivots rather than route changes or overlays?"
 ?[wonder]: "Which moments of structural revelation are strong enough to feel magical without violating calm defaults?"
 ?[authoring]: "What is the smallest authoring contract that lets a page become Spw-backed without requiring a full in-browser parser?"
 ?[interaction_personality]: "What is the signature quality of interaction on this site — handwriting, grammar, physics, something else? What does that imply for timing constants and transition behavior?"
 ?[spirit_phase_interaction]: "Should interaction sequences trace spirit phases? Which input mode most naturally embodies initiation, resistance, transformation, expression, or return — and should that tracing be legible or ambient?"
 ?[timing_vocabulary]: "Should timing tokens be named after Spw concepts (charge-decay, pivot-arc, boon-settle) rather than generic design-system durations — and would that naming change how implementers choose values?"
 ?[inspect_texture]: "What does inspecting a node on this site feel like — revealing language or revealing physical state? What does that imply for inspect animation and label placement?"
 ?[style_log_moment]: "At which commit should the first set of timing/transition constants be logged as explicit taste decisions in this stream rather than left as implementation details?"
}

^["commits"]{
 ~[1]: "#[mobile-runtime] - capture the planning artifacts and distilled semantics note"
 ~[2]: ".[semantics] - formalize UX invariants, prefix/postfix symmetry, brace physics, pivots, and register invariants"
 ~[3]: "&[runtime] - extract shared keyboard, interaction, and register runtime foundations from page-local behavior"
 ~[4]: "&[blocks] - add region/page hosts plus contracts for declarative blocks, scripts, and inspect surfaces"
 ~[5]: "![mobile-runtime] - verify coarse-pointer behavior, inspectability, and region containment"
}

